    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-30T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-30T05:00:00-05:00" n="609"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/805: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-30T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 30, 1943—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1098. In exercise of the discretion given to me in your 970, April 29, 11 p.m.
                        [<hi rend="italic">a.m.</hi>] I have authorized sailings proposed in my
                    1086, April 29, 2 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d609fn21">Not printed.</note> I am
                    prepared to justify to the President my decision in this regard which has been
                    made in the light of the President’s approval of our petroleum program and the
                    relation of that program to our entire policy toward Spain which is bringing
                    results of incalculable benefit to our war effort.</p>
                <p>In a subsequent telegram I shall outline my views in response to Department’s
                    958, April 27, 3 p.m. I request no categoric instructions limiting sailings or
                    loadings of Spanish tankers be issued prior to receipt and consideration of that
                    telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
